# Component Guidelines

## Component Structure
Components should be placed in `src/components/` and follow these conventions:

1. Use `.astro` extension for Astro components
2. Use TypeScript interfaces for props
3. Keep components focused and single-responsibility

## Example Component Structure
```astro
---
interface Props {
  // Define your props here
}

const { prop1, prop2 } = Astro.props;
---

<div>
  <!-- Component content -->
</div>

<style>
  /* Component styles */
</style>
```

## Common Components
- [Grid.astro](mdc:src/components/Grid.astro): A flexible grid layout component
- [Layout.astro](mdc:src/layouts/Layout.astro): Base layout template

## Best Practices
1. Use TypeScript for type safety
2. Keep styles scoped to components
3. Use props for component configuration
4. Document complex props with JSDoc comments
